The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, November 25, 2002  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, November 25, 2002				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	 Southern Avenue: Work is in progress on a drainage pumping station.				 																																	 Chowringhee Road: A flyover is coming up.				 																Films				 																																	 Preview of Bol, eight one-minute films on domestic violence, on International Day Protesting Violence Against Women, put together by Swayam. Other programmes include a play and a poster exhibition on Park Circus Maidan, from 2 pm to 7 pm.				 																Music				 																																	 Sarod recital by Rajeeb Chakraborty as part of Spicmacays Virasat 2002 at St. Thomas School for Girls, 1 pm.				 																Health				 																																	 Discussion on western and indigenous medicine at Corpus Research Institute, Jadavpur University, 11.45 am.				 																Art watch				 																																	 Works of Avijit Dutta, Tapas Ghosal and Shiladitya Sarkar presented by The Art Collector at 12C, Sunny Park, 3 pm-8 pm.				 																																	 Rare drawings of Amitabha Dhar, Hiran Mitra, Prabhat Basu, Tapas Konar and others at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, from 3 pm to 8 pm.				 																On stage				 																																	 Birpurush, presented by Chetna, at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm.				 																Workshop 				 																																	 Cookery workshop conducted by star chef Sanjeev Kapoor at the Grain of Salt Terrace Banquet, from 4 pm to 7 pm.
